1.2.	The State Customs Service attended existing international networks on issues of ODS import & export control and other necessary bilateral and exchange visits; 
The laboratory of the Customs Service, the Environmental Protection Inspectorate, 
Tajikstandart equipped with new equipment for the identification of HCFCs and HFCs.

1.3.	Standards and safety rules for natural refrigerants and HCF introduced and adapted/ applied; 

1.4.	Cooperation enhanced with RAC Association, and promoted long-term education of new members of Association and other technical specialists with new technologies using refrigerants with zero-ODP and low-GWP, including natural refrigerants; 
Ensured participation of 1-2 technical staff in network meetings and international conferences related to new technologies with zero-ODP and low-GWP, and energy efficiency (EE), which initially discussed and agreed with technical staff.

2.1	Strengthened capacity of 2 recycling centers for HCFC reuse and they fully functional. 
