Outcome#5: 
- In March 7, 2020, 4 trainers / RAC technicians (all men) received certificates on the special trainings-for-trainers on refrigerants with zero ODS and low GWP, to gain knowledge, in the selected training institute of Belarussian Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Association (APIMH) in the Republic of Belarus in order to instill the gained knowledge to other technicians in Tajikistan. The training was conducted from January 27 to March 7, 2020;  
After the successful graduation, trainers use the gained knowledge in their daily practices with their peers and technicians in the RAC sector in the regions by conducting learning sessions in order to share their gained knowledge on refrigerants with zero ODS and low GWP. Particularly, in November - December 2019, 4 training sessions (16 days) were held in all regions of the country, where 72 technicians (all men) participated and received certificates; 
By the October 2020, the UNDP HCFC project is expected to conduct trainings for 260 technicians, officers and specialists related to the ODS field (including 10-15 women), in identified regions of the country, with engagement of 2-3 trainers / RAC technicians who received special trainings-for-trainers on refrigerants with zero ODS and low GWP in the training institute of Belarussian Refrigeration and Air Conditioning Association (APIMH). 
 - In May 2020 the Letter of Agreement was signed between the UNDP and the State Educational Institution “Engineering-Pedagogical College of Dushanbe” of the Republic of Tajikistan on implementation of professional development/capacity building refresher training courses for 290 refrigeration and air conditioning technicians (RAC), including their certification on the “Safe and efficient use of flammable and toxic refrigerants, as well as technology for servicing and repairing refrigeration and air conditioning equipment with zero ozone-depleting potential, and with a low level of global warming potential, including natural refrigerants (propane, isobutane and ammonia”). 

Outcome#6: 
In 2020, the UNDP HCFC project has estimated and planned three (3) big tender cases under UNDP Procurement Annual Plan 2020, for procurement of necessary equipment for targeted recipients in order to ensure a good refrigerant management with the total amount of USD 92,000.00. The international specialist on zero ODP and low GWP energy efficient and low carbon technologies together with local technicians are working on development of the TOR and technical specifications of the new technologies and equipment to be procured before the end 2020.

Outcome#7: 
- Complete list and technical specifications for identification and analyzation RAC equipment developed and agreed with target beneficiary companies and stakeholder organizations as well as technician experts from RAC sector. Project has procured 6 sets of special equipment for ODS identification and analyzation and have been handed over to the Customs service units and mobile laboratories of the Customs, as well as for the inspection of the Committee for Environmental Protection under the Government of Tajikistan to prevent the illegal import of ODS (HCFCs) and ODS containing products and technologies (HCFCs).

Outcome#10: 
- Government identified a suitable ODS waste storage that is located in the Yavan district of the Khatlon province (oblast). Technical Coordinator of the HCFC-2 project visited the selected site in the Yavan and conducted a monitoring of the facility for the purpose to identify the adequate premise for re-construction under warehouse for temporary storage of ODS waste.  
-In accordance with the proposal of the Ministry of Industry and New Technologies of the Republic of Tajikistan, the approval of the Committee for Environmental Protection under the Government of the Republic of Tajikistan, and cooperation of the Open Joint-Stock Company (OJSC) “TAJIKKHIMPROM”, the United Nations Development Program in Tajikistan, in the framework of the project “Complete HCFC Phase-Out in Tajikistan through Promotion of zero ODP, low GWP, Energy Efficient Technologies” the UNDP HCFC project started to organize the work on selection and approval of the premises for establishment of a “warehouse for the temporary storage of ozone-depleting substances (ODS)” wastes on the territory of the OJSC “TAJIKKHIMPROM” in the Yavan district of the Republic of Tajikistan in accordance with the requirements of the regulations of state control bodies in the field of ODS waste storage. 
The project hired the Local Civil Engineer for rehabilitation of temporary ODS waste storage. The Local Engineer conducted technical assessment of the selected buildings and compiled technical documentation for “Rehabilitation of warehouse for temporary storage of ODS waste”. The rehabilitation of temporary ODS waste storage will be completed by 30.11.2020. 

