Outcome#12: 
- In April 8, 2020, under the framework of the current project, the Letter of Agreement was signed between the UNDP and the State Educational Institution “Engineering-Pedagogical College of Dushanbe” of the Republic of Tajikistan on professional development/capacity building refresher training courses for 290 refrigeration and air conditioning (RAC) technicians, including their certification on the “Safe and efficient use of flammable and toxic refrigerants, as well as technology for servicing and repairing refrigeration and air conditioning equipment with zero ozone-depleting potential, and with a low level of global warming potential, including natural refrigerants (propane, isobutane and ammonia)”. 

Under the signed LOA, it is envisaged that the Technical colleges will disseminate information and inspire RAC technicians, particularly young women, to apply for training courses in Technical college. Moreover, to ensure high enrolment and attendance of young women, the Technical college and UNDP will cover the costs of whole training course and also will set-up a stipend mechanism to attract and to encourage young women to apply for RAC trainings, and onward being self-engaged/ self-employed in RAC sector as whole.  
 - In close cooperation with the Committee for Women and Family Affairs, the project will elaborate a strategy on the involvement of women in RAC activities, particularly in managing small business, receive and record orders, maintain contact details and office management. 
The project is working toward gender outreach and awareness raising activities in order to contribute to gender quality, by introducing a new affordable educational programme for young women in affordable technical colleges and educational institution. Thus, the project is hiring national Gender Outreach Specialist. 
Data collection and analysis of Gender Experts on the level and rate of enrollment and participation of the young women in technical training courses in Technical colleges

